│ "llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VectorCombine.cpp"]], "thoughts": "1.          │
│ Understanding the Issue:\nThe crash is an assertion failure in                │
│ isSingleSourceMaskImpl: it asserts that each shuffle mask element must be     │
│ within [0, NumOpElts*2). In our reproducer,                                   │
│ VectorCombine::foldInsExtVectorToShuffle, when handling a length-changing     │
│ combine (source <16 x i8> to destination <4 x i8>), constructs an             │
│ ExtToVecMask for a SK_PermuteSingleSrc cost query with a mask element set to  │
│ 11 (the extract index) while using Ty = <4 x i8>. This is out of bounds for   │
│ the 4-lane context used by TargetTransformInfo's improveShuffleKindFromMask   │
│ (NumSrcElts=4), causing the assertion.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\n- The pass │
│ visits the insertelement and immediately crashes during cost modeling (no IR  │
│ changed yet).\n- Backtrace shows the crash originates from                    │
│ improveShuffleKindFromMask calling ShuffleVectorInst::isReverseMask, which    │
│ calls isSingleSourceMaskImpl and asserts on the mask element value.\n- The    │
│ problematic query is TTI.getShuffleCost(SK_PermuteSingleSrc, DstVecTy=<4 x    │
│ i8>, ExtToVecMask=[11, poison, poison, poison]).\n\n3. Root Cause             │
│ Analysis:\n- improveShuffleKindFromMask assumes the operand size equals the   │
│ result vector size (it uses Ty->getElementCount() to compute NumSrcElts).     │
│ This is stated in the helper functions (\"We don't have vector operand size   │
│ information, so assume operands are the same size as the mask\").\n-          │
│ VectorCombine, however, passed a mask containing an element (11) larger than  │
│ 2*NumDstElts-1 for the SK_PermuteSingleSrc cost query when modeling a         │
│ length-changing shuffle. This makes the mask invalid for TTI’s classification │
│ helpers and triggers the assertion.\n- Therefore, the bug is in               │
│ VectorCombine’s cost modeling: it must not pass out-of-range mask indices to  │
│ TTI when Ty is the smaller destination vector.\n\n4. Proposed Edit            │
│ Point(s)\n- File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VectorCombine.cpp\n-          │
│ Location: In VectorCombine::foldInsExtVectorToShuffle, in the NeedExpOrNarrow │
│ path where ExtToVecMask is prepared for the SK_PermuteSingleSrc cost          │
│ query.\n- Change: When ExtIdx is out of bounds for NumDstElts, clamp the mask │
│ index into the legal range for Ty to avoid out-of-bounds indices in TTI       │
│ classification.\n\nEdit:\n- Before: ExtToVecMask[0] = ExtIdx;\n- After:       │
│ ExtToVecMask[0] = static_cast<int>(ExtIdx % NumDstElts);\n\nRationale: This   │
│ guarantees the mask indices are within [0, NumDstElts-1] for the              │
│ single-source cost query, satisfying isSingleSourceMaskImpl. It preserves the │
│ intent of modeling a generic length-changing shuffle cost without relying on  │
│ operand sizes that TTI does not see. Broadcasting or generic permute          │
│ classification remains acceptable for cost modeling; importantly, it avoids   │
│ the assertion while keeping costs conservative.\n\n5. Conclusion:\nBy         │
│ clamping the out-of-range mask element when NeedExpOrNarrow is true, we       │
│ prevent TTI’s improveShuffleKindFromMask from asserting on invalid indices.   │
│ This fix keeps cost modeling valid and allows the transformation to proceed   │
│ or be rejected based on cost without crashing. The functional IR remains      │
│ unchanged; only the internal cost query mask is sanitized."})                 │
